15/02/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A police officer with the multi-ethnic force was seriously injured in a car bombing Sunday (February 14th) in the southern town of Bujanovac. The device was planted under his car. He was identified as Bljerim Mustafa. The policeman's wife was also in injured in the blast, along with two passersby. Interior Minister Ivica Dacic condemned the bombing as a terrorist act. (RTS, B92, DPA - 15/02/10)

